# Security & GDPR

## Personal Data Protection

Members' personal data (name, email, phone, birth date, height) requires:

- Explicit consent before collection
- Encryption at rest for sensitive fields (email, phone)
- Right to deletion (hard delete on request)
- Data export capability (GDPR Article 20)
- Audit log for data access

## Authentication

- Passwords: bcrypt cost 12+
- JWT with refresh tokens (access: 15min, refresh: 7d dashboard / 30d PWA)
- Rate limiting: 100 req/15min per IP on auth endpoints
- Account lockout after 5 failed attempts
- SSE endpoints: JWT via query param `?token=<jwt>` (EventSource limitation)
  - Short-lived tokens mitigate query param exposure
  - HTTPS enforced in production

## API Security

- CORS: only known origins
- Helmet.js for security headers
- Input validation via class-validator on ALL endpoints
- Never expose internal IDs in error messages
- Never log personal data (mask in logs)

## Secrets

- NEVER commit `.env` files
- All secrets via environment variables
- Database connection string, JWT secret, FCM keys = env vars only
